 checks.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering hostname encoding**\\n\\nI'm thinking about calculating the length of the hostname using `hostName.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8).length`. If the hostname is ASCII, that should work just fine, but I have to consider that it might also contain Unicode characters. However, I’m leaning toward using ASCII here since hostname requirements generally call for that. In this case, I don’t think I need to complicate things unnecessarily.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_h82m9nYeOqHcY5fMcuLgZZh8|fc_002802e41ad4bd860169f4da9bef588192922ef99d06089288", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests -name AGENTS.md -print"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find tests -name AGENTS.md -print\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 312, "output": 1019, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33075, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777654413272, "responseId": "resp_002802e41ad4bd860169f4da8da6448192a577381a535fbfcc"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_h82m9nYeOqHcY5fMcuLgZZh8|fc_002802e41ad4bd860169f4da9bef588192922ef99d06089288", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/AGENTS.md\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777654428805}]}
